Q1 : Where does ArrayList store data internally and why?
Ans : ArrayList internally stores elements in an Object[] array. It uses an object array because in Java every class
      is a child of Object, so this allows ArrayList to store any type of object.
      If interviewer asks for example
      Example:
      In an employee management system, initially we may store name and age, later we may need address, salary, or
      department. Since different types of data may be stored, ArrayList uses Object[] internally to store any object.
